A year ago today I was pretty sick with covid-19, and my partner and I spent the (United States) Thanksgiving holiday alone and pretty sick out here where we live. The symptoms lingered into 2021, but I started the 30 Day Breath journey on 1/1/21 along with daily meditation, and I slowly got better. I have continued to practice some of your 30 Day journeys all year, as well as the Chakra Ride and some others. I didn't practice every day and my health (and family life) suffered a few setbacks, but I practiced with you at least 100 days, maybe more. I realize now that this work has (while never feeling like work, but rather like love) really changed me inside and out. Here we are on the night before Thanksgiving, nearing the end of a very hard year all over the world, and now I'm also in my final week of True, and I just want to thank you SO MUCH for all the work and love that you give us all. I am so incredibly grateful. My mantra today was "be more in my body" and when you said "now believe that it's already true", I realized...it is! I have become much more in my body this past year. I teach t'ai chi and karate now, I just started a daily dance practice, and, well, I just feel more balanced in myself, centered, more me, moving inside and out. Thank you. üß° May peace and love surround you this holiday season, and may you feel as buoyant and balanced as you help us all to feel! Namaste.

Thank you, Adriene, from the very bottom of my heart. I've been practicing yoga with you for over 3 years now, and I have formed a deep-rooted appreciation for you and yoga. You've introduced such a beautiful art to me, and there's no way I can thank you enough. Along with sharing the art of yoga, you are astonishingly talented at guiding others through it. I just did this episode, and I was feeling very negative about myself. I suffer from severe anxiety and social anxiety, so I constantly overthink and analyze my behavior, tone, body language, etc. This causes me to notice unimportant flaws in myself that every human would have and dismiss in a heartbeat (I mean just the human species; of course you all worry about yourselves too, I just meant things that people with less anxiety would dismiss, like maybe speaking a few slurred words, or stuttering a bit.). At 3:34 , I think, you reassured me and told me that I should feel my feelings, and be true to myself. Adriene, your ability to connect with others so deeply (and VIRTUALLY!) continues to startle me. You are such a positive figure in my life, and I couldn't express enough how amazing you are. Yoga has been like a medication for my anxiety and other mental issues. Let me specify. YOUR yoga videos have been like a medication for my anxiety and other mental issues. Without you, I wouldn't have discovered who I am. Without you, I probably wouldn't be here today and now. The impact you've had on my life is immense. Thank you, again, from the bottom of my heart, and keep guiding others through the art of yoga. 

- Willow Branchflower

Here's a funny note on the hand positions: my go-to was to mirror your image on the screen first, i.e. my left hand up right hand down. Natural position for me, playing stringed instruments, I've always had a relationship with the left fingers up, right fingers down position, where the right is the structure (rhythm) and left is the more free (notes) part. So the funny aha for me, I've been playing a lot of piano recently and when we switched hands, I realized that piano is the opposite, left had down is the structural part, right hand (well, it's down when you're actually playing the keys of course,) the more free high part.¬†

I've been practicing yoga with Adriene for about 16 months now, and when I stop and think of the changes it's made in my life and in my body. I couldn't sit on my heels, now I can. My upper arm strength was weak, but I'm noticing changes and definition. I rarely have troubles sleeping, because I've learned to use my breath to calm me. When I run, I get into the rhythm of my breath, so while I still listen to music, I am not dependent on the beat to propel me forward, I depend on my breath. I never notice  these changes while they're happening, but little by little I do. Like today, when I finished out sitting on my heels as opposed to finding a blanket or a towel to cushion. I'm amazed at my almost 51 year old body every day.

In the end of this practice when you asked if I can feel any energy or tension in my body I didn't feel anything at all, I only felt peace. For the first time in my life I felt pure peace. So calm and beautiful, so perfect and alive. Thank you for guiding me to those places in my mind and body.
